len]]''|''[[Comics Unleashed]]''}}\n}}\n| module2            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Byron Allen Folks'''<ref name=courthousenews>{{cite news|url= https://www.courthousenews.com/comics-say-producer-byron-allen-is-no-joke/|title=Comics Say Producer Byron Allen Is No Joke|date=December 27, 2012|agency=[[Courthouse News Service]]|first=Rebekah|last=Kearn|accessdate=April 23, 2020|archivedate=April 23, 2020|archiveurl = http://archive.is/Ivdcx|url-status=live}}</ref> is an [[United States|American]] businessman, former [[comedian]], [[television producer]], philanthropist, and the head of the [[United States|U.S.]] entertainment company [[Entertainment Studios|Allen Media Group]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nAllen's interest in show business began during his childhood, when he would accompany his mother, Carolyn Folks,<ref name=variety2019>{{cite magazine|url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200326050315/https://variety.com/2019/tv/features/byron-allen-entertainment-studios-still-very-acquisitive-1203117363/|title=Byron Allen Is Still 'Very Acquisitive' After Transformative Year|first= Robert |last=Marich|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020|archivedate=March 26, 2020| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326050315/https://variety.com/2019/tv/features/byron-allen-entertainment-studios-still-very-acquisitive-1203117363/|url-status=live}}</ref> to NBC studios in Burbank where she worked as a publicist.<ref name=\"Sentinel\">{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Allan|title=Byron Allen Followed Destiny (and Carson) into Late Night TV|url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1992-11-13/lifestyle/9211120119_1_byron-allen-allen-show-allen-explains|newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]|via=''[[Orlando Sentinel]]''|archivedate=October 19, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20161019144153/http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1992-11-13/lifestyle/9211120119_1_byron-allen-allen-show-allen-explains|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAt age 14, Allen put together his first stand-up routine and began appearing on amateur night at comedy clubs throughout the [[Los Angeles]] area.<ref name=\"Sentinel\"/>\n\n==Career==\nComedian [[Jimmie Walker]] saw Allen's stand-up act and invited the 14-year-old comedian to join his comedy writing team alongside promising young comedians [[Jay Leno]] and [[David Letterman]]. At age 18, Allen made his television debut on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson]]''. One of his earliest roles was as a regular presenter on the NBC series ''[[Real People]]'' during the show's entire run.\n\nHis show ''Jammin'' was picked up as ''Kickin' It with Byron Allen'' in 1992, and by the end of its run had made the [[list of longest-running United States television series]]. Allen's foray into television production began in Los Angeles in 1993 when he founded [[Entertainment Studios]] with the launch of his first series \u2014 ''[[Entertainers with Byron Allen]]'' \u2014 a weekly, one-hour series profiling the current stars of film and television.\n\nIn 2019, he partnered with [[Sinclair Broadcast Group]] in Diamond Holding Group to acquire [[Fox Sports Networks]], which [[The Walt Disney Company]] agreed to sell as a condition of its [[Disney acquisition of Fox|purchase of 21st Century Fox]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/sinclair-disney-regional-sports-network-deal-1203204685/|title=Sinclair Clinches Disney-Regional Sports Networks Deal, Byron Allen Joins as Partner|last=Littleton|first=Cynthia|last2=Littleton|first2=Cynthia|date=2019-05-03|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-05-05}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nIn 2018, Allen was selected for the Bloomberg 50 as one of \"the people in business, entertainment, finance, politics, and technology and science whose 2018 accomplishments were particularly noteworthy.\"<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/features/2018-bloomberg-50/|title=The Bloomberg 50 > Byron Allen|magazine=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]|access-date=February 20, 2020|archivedate=March 26, 2020|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200326050408/https://www.bloomberg.com/features/2018-bloomberg-50/|url-status=live}}</ref> He was also selected for the 100 Most Intriguing Entrepreneurs at the Goldman Sachs Builders & Innovators Summit 2018, and he was honored as a Distinguished Guest Speaker at the Salvation Army Christmas Kettle Luncheon in December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://christmaskettleluncheon.org/honoree/|title=Honoree \u2013 Christmas Kettle Luncheon|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-18}}</ref> In January 2019, Allen was a recipient of NATPE's 16th Annual Brandon Tartikoff Legacy Awards,{{cn|date=April 2020}} presented during the annual NATPE Miami Marketplace & Conference. Allen received the 2019 Whitney M. Young Jr. Award{{cn|date=April 2020}} at the 46th annual Los Angeles Urban League Awards dinner.\n\n==Personal life==\nAllen married Jennifer Lucas in 2007.<ref>{{cite magazine | url= https://people.com/celebrity/talk-show-host-byron-allen-marries-tv-producer/| magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] | accessdate=March 1, 2020| title=Talk Show Host Byron Allen Marries TV Producer | first=Ulrica | last=Wihlborg | date=September 1, 2007}}</ref> The couple has three children: two daughters born in 2008<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Wihlborg |first=Ulrica |url=https://people.com/parents/talk-show-host-byron-allen-wife-welcome-a-girl/|title=Talk Show Host Byron Allen & Wife Welcome a Girl|magazine=People|date=2008-09-26 |accessdate=2020-03-01}}</ref> and 2010,<ref>{{cite magazine|url= https://people.com/parents/byron-allen-welcomes-daughter-olivia-rose/|title=Byron Allen Welcomes Daughter |magazine=People |date=2010-04-08 |accessdate=2014-05-23}}</ref> and a son born in 2012.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Byron Allen Welcomes Son Lucas Byron |url=https://people.com/parents/byron-allen-welcomes-son-lucas-byron/amp/ |magazine=People |accessdate=March 1, 2020 |date=December 12, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0020334|title=Byron Allen}}\n*[http://www.es.tv/ Entertainment Studios]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Allen, Byron}}\n[[Category:Entertainment Studios]]\n[[Category:African-American television personalities]]\n[[Category:African-American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American television producers]]\n[[Category:American television talk show hosts]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American chief executives in the media industry]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American comedian}}\n{{Use American English|date = February 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date = February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name = Byron Allen\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| image_upright      = \n| landscape          = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name = Byron Allen Folks\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place        = \n| baptised           = <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered -->\n| disappeared_date   = <!-- {{Disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place  = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (enter DEATH date then BIRTH date (e.g., ...|1908|31|8|1967|28|2}} use both this parameter and |birth_date to display the person's date of birth, date of death, and age at death) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| b